When working with the Build Participation feature in php I noticed that syntax errors don't appear on the ruler (next to the line numbers) when created. Saving the file will cause the errors to be displayed in the problems pane as well as on the ruler.

Steps to reproduce:
1) In a PHP file define a function that concatenates several strings together
{noformat}
$size = "small";
$color = "red";
function flight($size, $color){
	echo "This " . $size . " " . $color . " bird can fly.";
}
{noformat}
2) Remove one of the concatenation operators.
{noformat}
<?php

$size = "small";
$color = "red";
function flight($size, $color){
	echo "This " . $size . " " . $color " bird can fly.";
}

?>
{noformat}
