We should support using ftp URIs in the EFS filesystem API using our existing infrastructure. Forget handling passwords/prefs, just assume the URI contains the info needed to connect (i.e. login/password/port/host).

Users will be able to see/use this in the HTML editor by trying to get Content Assist on a public anonymous FTP site, by enter in:
{code}
<a href="ftp://3dftp.com/|"></a>
{code}

and then hitting Ctrl+Space at the | (which is where the cursor should be, not something user actually types) and getting back the folders "pub", "incoming" and "conf" as options.

